<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10138i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10138i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10138i"> 138(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> 1 side of his face / in shadow</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mercure <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Dans quelques peintures, on le voit avec <mark>la moiti&eacute; du visage claire, et l&apos;autre noire et sombre</mark>: ce qui indique que tant&ocirc;t il est dans le ciel ou sur la terre, tant&ocirc;t dans les Enfers o&ugrave; il conduit les &acirc;mes des morts. <font color="green">[In some paintings he is seen with with half of his face bright, the other half dark and sombre, indicating that sometimes he is in the sky or on earth, sometimes in Hades, where he leads the souls of the dead.]</font> <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 61</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01068d" href="c01all.htm#c01068d">VI.C.01:068(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
